    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>The range of <i>Festuca brachyphylla</i> includes high elevations in the Mono (341D) and Southeastern Great Basin (341F).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Eo). Stands at Rae Lakes Basin in Sequoia National Park (Burke 1982) characterize the alliance in California.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> These alpine stands are typically small and remote with few effects from human activities. However, climatic change may affect the viability and locations of stands. </div>
</div>

    

    

